    <article xml:id="notes">
        <section xml:id="sec-field-extensions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
            <title>Field-extensions</title>
            <theorem xml:id="thm-iso-simple-field-extensions">
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Suppose that <m>\sigma\colon F\to F'</m> is an isomorphism of fields. Let <m>p\in F[x]</m> be an irreducible polynomial and let <m>p'\in F'[x]</m> be a polynomial obtained from <m>p</m> by applying <m>\sigma</m> to coefficients of <m>p</m>. If <m>\alpha</m> (resp., <m>\beta</m>) is a root of <m>p</m> (resp., <m>p'</m>) in some field extension of <m>F</m> (resp., <m>F'</m>), then there is an isomorphism <m>\widetilde{\sigma}\colon F(\alpha)\to F'(\beta)</m>.
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </theorem>
            <proof>
                <p>
                    Note that <m>p'</m> is also irreducible. Indeed, <m>\sigma</m> induces an isomorphism of rings <m>F[x]\simeq F'[x]</m> by defining <m>\sum a_ix^i\mapsto\sum\sigma(a_i)x^i</m>. We have the following commutative diagram.
                </p>
                <figure xml:id="fig-iso-simple-field-extensions">
                    <caption>a</caption>
                    <image width="50%">
                        <shortdescription>a</shortdescription>
                        <latex-image>
                            \begin{tikzpicture}
                                \node(F){$F$};
                                \node(x)[right=of F]{$F[x]$};
                                \draw[->] (F) to node [swap] {$i$} (x);
                                \node(p)[right of = x]{$F[x]/(p)$};
                                \draw[->] (x) to node [swap] {$\pi_F$} (p);
                                \node(a) [right of = p]{$F(\alpha)$};
                                \draw[->] (p) to node [swap] {$\ev_\alpha$} (a);
                                <!--\node(FF)[below of = F]{$F'$};
                                \node(y)[right of = FF]{$F'[y]$};
                                \draw[->] (FF) to node [swap] {$i'$} (y);
                                \node(p')[right of = y, below of = x]{$F'[y]/(p')$};
                                \draw[->] (y) to node [swap] {$\pi_{F'}$} (p');
                                \node(b) [right of = p']{$F'(\beta)$};
                                \draw[->] (p') to node [swap] {$\ev_\beta$} (b);
                                \draw[->] (F) to node {$\sigma$} (FF);
                                \draw[->] (x) to node {$\sigma$} (y);
                                \draw[->] (p) to node {$\sigma$} (p');
                                \draw[->,dashed] (a) to node {$\sigma$} (b);-->
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                        </latex-image>
                    </image>
                </figure>
            </proof>
        </section>
